edu.umass.cs.msocket.proxy.location

Class GlobalCoordinate

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.umass.cs.msocket.proxy.location.GlobalCoordinate
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<GlobalCoordinate>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GlobalPosition

    public class GlobalCoordinate
extends Object
implements Comparable<GlobalCoordinate>, Serializable

    Encapsulation of latitude and longitude coordinates on a globe. Negative latitude is southern hemisphere. Negative longitude is western hemisphere.

    Any angle may be specified for longtiude and latitude, but all angles will be canonicalized such that: 

     -90 <= latitude <= +90 - 180 < longitude <= +180
    Author:
    Mike Gavaghan
    See Also:
